# /optimize-claude Command Implementation

## Metadata
- **Date**: 2025-11-14
- **Feature**: New /optimize-claude command with multi-stage research and planning workflow
- **Scope**: Create standalone command that delegates to research agents (CLAUDE.md + docs analysis) followed by planning agent
- **Estimated Phases**: 6
- **Complexity**: Medium
- **Standards File**: /home/benjamin/.config/CLAUDE.md
- **Related Commands**: /plan, /implement, /coordinate
- **Related Agents**: claude-md-analyzer (new), docs-structure-analyzer (new), cleanup-plan-architect (new)
- **Pattern Reference**: Similar to /coordinate but simpler (2 research agents → 1 planning agent, no flags)

## Overview

Create a new `/optimize-claude` command that provides intelligent CLAUDE.md and documentation analysis. The command uses a **multi-stage agent workflow** following the /coordinate pattern but simplified with no flags.

**Simple Usage**:
```bash
/optimize-claude  # No flags needed
```

**Workflow**:

**Stage 1: Parallel Research** (2 agents)
1. **claude-md-analyzer**: Analyzes CLAUDE.md structure, section sizes, metadata usage
2. **docs-structure-analyzer**: Analyzes .claude/docs/ organization, existing files, integration points

**Stage 2: Sequential Planning** (1 agent)
3. **cleanup-plan-architect**: Reads both research reports and creates comprehensive optimization plan improving both CLAUDE.md and .claude/docs/

**Stage 3: Present Results**
4. Display plan location and next steps (no interactive prompts)

### Success Criteria
- [ ] Three new specialized agents created following agent development guide
- [ ] New /optimize-claude command created (.claude/commands/optimize-claude.md)
- [ ] Command has no flag parsing (simple invocation only)
- [ ] Command invokes research agents in parallel (Stage 1)
- [ ] Command includes verification checkpoints after research (Stage 1)
- [ ] Command invokes planning agent with report paths (Stage 2)
- [ ] Planning agent produces structured refactoring plan in topic-based spec directory
- [ ] User receives plan path and can run /implement manually
- [ ] All changes follow project standards (imperative language, verification checkpoints, behavioral injection)
- [ ] Tests validate all three agents and command workflow
- [ ] Documentation updated (new optimize-claude-command-guide.md, agent-reference.md)

## Technical Design

